<HEADLINE>
THIS WEEK'S TV HIGHLIGHTS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TODAY: The Avalanche's record with Ray Borque is ... hey, forget
that for a second. Without him, they're 3-0 in the playoffs. His
injured leg may not be ready for him to come back tonight, but if
he doesn't ... let's just say, the Avs aren't that worried anymore.
NHL playoffs: Colorado at Dallas, Game 2; ESPN, 4 p.m. (ESPN has
Game 3 at Colorado, Friday at 5 p.m. and ABC has Game 4, Sunday at
noon) &QL; 
TUESDAY: No matter how many times you think a sweep will happen,
something comes along to goof it up. Then again, Jerry Buss isn't
complaining about another night of revenue. NBA playoffs: Phoenix
at Lakers, Game 5, FSN, 7:30 p.m. (If necessary, Channel 9 and TNT
have Thursday's Game 6 from Phoenix and NBC has Saturday's Game 7
from L.A.). &QL; 
WEDNESDAY: Tonight, a very special two-hour series finale of
``Beverly Hills 90210.'' But before that, Fox's other franchise
from Beverly Hills, Kevin Brown, pitches a day game at Wrigley
Field. When he's through with his latest no-decision, he's no doubt
inviting the brass back to his hotel suite for a viewing party.
MLB: Dodgers at Chicago, FSN2, 11:15 a.m. (FSN2 also has Tuesday's
Dodgers-Cubs game at 5 p.m. and Thursday's game at 11:15 a.m.) &QL; 
THURSDAY: New Jersey's Larry Robinson used to coach the Kings. So
did Roger Neilsen (although the Flyers have elected to keep him off
the bench as he recovers from cancer treatment). And Barry Melrose,
another Kings coach, will be giving his opinions on the series for
ESPN. What does it all mean? Andy Murray has a great future ahead
of him. NHL playoffs: Philadelphia at New Jersey, Game 3; ESPN,
4:30 p.m. (ESPN also has Tuesday's Game 2 from Philadelphia at 4
p.m. and Saturday's Game 4 from New Jersey at 4:30 p.m.) &QL; 
FRIDAY: After five consecutive losses to begin their AFL existence,
this is the game they're finally gonna win. If there's anything we
have to avenge, it's Houston getting the NFL over L.A. Arena
Football League: Houston at Avengers, FSN2, 7 p.m. &QL; 
SATURDAY: The last three horses who won the Kentucky Derby - Silver
Charm, Real Quiet and Charismatic - also won the Preakness but fell
short of winning the Belmont Stakes in the final strides. But none
of them was the favorite in the Derby like Fusaichi Pegasus. The
Foo Fighter, everyone's Triple Crown favorite now, best not reveal
any weakness in the Preakness or he'll shatter too many dreams.
Horse racing: Preakness Stakes, Channel 7, 2:27 p.m. &QL; 
SUNDAY: So there'll be Elgin ``EBay'' Baylor in a familiar spot -
sitting behind the Clippers logo, clueless, waiting to see if they
have enough Ping-Pong balls to get the No.1 overall choice. Then,
in a new twist, they offer the pick on the Internet to the highest
bidder. NBA draft lottery, Channel 4, approx. 1:30 p.m. (at
halftime of the 12:30 p.m. playoff game in this slot). &QL;
</P>
