<P>
   JOEMURRAY-COLUMN _ LUFKIN, Texas _ I was walking up from the far
part of the back yard. My wife was waiting at the door. When I was
hardly halfway to the house, she yelled to me. ``There's a bird in
the bedroom.'' A bird in the house. Oh me, oh my. I can sympathize
with a bird in a house. (Murray, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ In California, Steven
Vincent Bell laughed out loud when a county judge invoked the
``three strikes and you're out'' law and sentenced him to
35-years-to-life in prison for stealing a bicycle. Even ``60
Minutes'' got into the act and elevated the thief to national fame
as a result of what they felt to be a prime-time example of
judicial folly. (Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   LANE-COLUMN _ DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. _ Florida has the best
day-to-day weather around, but the megaweather is a killer. People
in other states speak nonchalantly about weather in the easy
short-term. They complain about a sudden late freeze in April. We
complain about oceanic-temperature cycles brewing monster
hurricanes. (Lane, Daytona Beach News-Journal). MOVED
</P>
