farmland has been a chronic concern in California since the end of
World War II as urbanization eats up orchards, vineyards and
vegetable fields in Santa Clara, Orange, San Bernardino and other
counties where agriculture once predominated. Farmers have been
compelled to become more efficient. By ERIC BRAZIL.
