<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-15 13:36 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5468 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u v BC-FEATURE-BUDGET-ART-BO     05-15 1033
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FEATURE-BUDGET-ART-BOS </SLUG>
  
 ART ADV.: Photos with SISTERS-INTERRUPTED and a graphic with
GUN-CONTROL are being transmitted to NYT Photo Service
subscribers.  
 For Immediate Release  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following FEATURE stories for
use by NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, please contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta
 &LR; at the Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of
graphics or photos please call  &UR; 888-346-9867  &LR; or  &UR; 888-603-1036 &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   POPE-SUCCESSOR (Undated) _ As John Paul II's 80th birthday
approaches, interviews suggest the next pope will not be an
American, will be 70-plus, will be conservative but not as
doctrinaire, and will be media-savvy. By Michael Paulson and Jeff
Israely. (2 takes)
</P>
<P>
   FOREIGN-JOURNAL (Tallinn, Estonia) _ To the police, the Voitka
brothers are ordinary robbery suspects. But the siblings have
become folk heroes. By Brian Whitmore. 540 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   SOCIAL-SECURITY (Washington) _ Neither George W. Bush nor Al
