<P>
   ISRAEL-PALESTINIANS _ RAMALLAH, West Bank _ In the worst
fighting since September 1997, Palestinian police and Israeli
soldiers engaged in an hours-long gun battle in the streets of this
West Bank city. The fighting started after rock-throwing
Palestinians clashed with Israeli soldiers to mark the Palestinian
anniversary, ``Catastrophe'' _ or the declaration of Israeli
independence in 1948. It also came on a day in which Israeli Prime
Minister Ehud Barak was expected to propose turning over more land
to the Palestinian Authority. But Palestinian frustrations have
been running high for months as peace talks have stalled, and
Palestinian prisoners in Israeli jails began a hunger strike. There
have already been reports of dead and injured. Developing. (Kaplow,
Cox News Service). 20.
</P>
<P>
   G8-CYBERCRIME _ PARIS _ Spot coverage of the European Union's
three-day Cyber-crime conference. More Tk. (Roughton, Cox News
Service). 18.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (i) International and (f) Financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-YOUTHVOTE _ MEXICO CITY _ About 10 million new and young
voters have been added to Mexico's voting population since the 1994
presidential election. They're a significant electoral bloc and
polls are showing they are favoring right-leaning candidate Vicente
Fox heavily. What's this new generation like? Are they less afraid
of the Institutional Revolutionary Party (PRI) and change?
(Ferriss, Cox News Service). 30. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   GRAPHICS: With box information attached to end of story.
</P>
<P>
   EDS: Expected to move by 2 p.m. EDT.
</P>
