formally nominated as a senate candidate at the New York Democratic
convention. Not that anyone will notice. From New York City to
Albany, only one word is on people's lips: Rudy. New York Mayor
Giuliani may have more to say in the next couple of hours about his
plans. Yesterday, he said a Newsweek report that he's dropping out
of the U.S. Senate race is ``totally inaccurate.'' The report says
Giuliani's course of treatment for prostate cancer will force him
to give up his campaign against Hillary Rodham Clinton. (Vejnoska,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
