<HEADER>
A5561 &Cx1f; ttg-z
u a BC-BROWN-COMPUTER-COLUMN     05-15 0436
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BROWN-COMPUTER-COLUMN-NYTR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DATABASE: 
LEXMARK MAKES HIGH RES, LOW COST PRINTER
</HEADLINE>
   By LONNIE BROWN   
 The Ledger, Lakeland, Fla.   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Back in the old days of computing _ when entire programs fit on
one floppy disk _ printer resolution was measured in terms of pins.
The nine-pin printer had nine pins that jabbed at a ribbon and made
letters on paper. The 24-pin printer was a vast improvement. More
pins meant smoother text and pictures.
</P>
<P>
   Pin-type printers have gone the way of green-and-black monitor
screens. They've been replaced by ink-jet printers that have far
higher resolution, are cheaper, print faster and print in full
color (something the pin printers did in their later years, but
with limited success).
</P>
<P>
   The highest resolution in the industry is built by Lexmark,
which uses ink cartridges with 1200-by-1200 dots-per-inch
resolution. The company announced this month that its new consumer
ink-jet, the Z52, will have a resolution of 2400-by-1200 dpi and
carry a street price of around $180.
</P>
<P>
   A company spokesman said the high resolution can be printed on
plain paper (rather than the more expensive photo variety).
However, the best results will probably come from using the special
photo paper, particularly when printing photographs from
high-resolution cameras.
</P>
<P>
   It's also fast. The Z52 can produce a gray-scale page every four
seconds (15 pages a minute). It will print 7 pages a minute in
color.
</P>
<P>
   For Apple users, there is additional good news. The printer has
the normal printer-port connector, but also has Universal Serial
Bus support so it can be connected to newer Macintosh systems.
</P>
<P>
   The printer uses the same paper-handling system that reduces
paper jams, the same design as the popular Z51 printer that is
currently at the top of PC World's Top 10 Printer List.
</P>
<P>
   A Lexmark spokesman said the new printer has the highest
durability cycle of any Lexmark inkjet printers. Although priced
for the home market, the printer also can handle small-business
tasks, like dual-side printing. Since the printer only prints on
one side of the paper at a time, the pages have to be run through
the printer a second time.
</P>
<P>
   The Z52 will be available in major retail stores handling
computers and electronics. It carries a one-year warranty with a
next-business-day exchange.
</P>
<P>
   For information, visit the company's Web site: www.lexmark.com.
</P>
<P>
   (Lonnie Brown is associate editor of The Ledger in Lakeland,
Fla. He can be reached by e-mail at LonnieB001(AT)aol.com. The
Ledger is a member of the New York Times Regional Newspapers.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-05-15-00 1504EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
