<P>
   (UNDATED) _ Famine, floods, poverty, pestilence _ such is the
fate of Africa it seems. Most seriously, wars still rage from north
to south and east to west. No one can blame Africans for the
weather, but most of the dark continent's shortcomings owe less to
acts of God than to acts of man. These acts are not exclusively
African _ brutality, despotism and corruption exist everywhere _
but African societies, for reasons buried in their cultures, seem
especially susceptible to them. &QL;
