<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Flattened homes and overturned cars _ not
exactly the images tourism officials plaster on travel brochures.
But the scenes of devastation from recent tornadoes are luring some
foreigners to the United States to spend vacations jaunting through
Tornado Alley. Customers of the Colorado-based Storm Chasing
Adventure Tours fork out $2,000 for a two-week trip chasing severe
weather in a radar-equipped van. By CRYSTAL YEDNAK. Story has moved
