<P>
   UNDATED _ The Bush-haters must be discouraged. They haven't been
swamping me with nasty e-mails, scathing letters and vitriolic
phone calls. These folks object to being described as
``Bush-haters,'' by the way. ``I don't hate George W. Bush,'' they
always say. ``I just don't think that stupid, smug, smirking
so-and-so is qualified to be president of the United States.'' What
do you suppose they'd say if they hated him? By BILL THOMPSON.
