BABY (Phoenix) - A jury on Monday found for two doctors who had
been accused of failing to diagnose a Phoenix woman's pregnancy
before it was too late for her to have an abortion. The nine-member
jury, comprised of seven men and two women, deliberated for about
30 minutes before rendering their decision. Ruth Ann Burns was
suing Dr. Leroy Kareus, Burns' family physician, and Dr. David
Kaufman, her obstetrician, for failing to detect and date the
pregnancy of her now 2-year-old son, Nicholas, in time to have an
