   NY-INDIAN-LANDCLAIMS (Onondaga Nation, N.Y.) _ The six Iroquois
nations of New York state are at the epicenter of one of the
biggest, most volatile issues now in upstate New York: Indian
claims to land that was seized 200 years ago. By David W. Chen.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
