<HEADLINE>
JETS' VITAL EXPECTED TO BE NAMED PATRIOTS NATIONAL SCOUT 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By NICK CAFARDO  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FOXBOROUGH, Mass. _ Bill Belichick will make one of the most
significant front office hires of his short Patriots reign when he
names New York Jets scout Lionel Vital the team's national pro
scout this week.
</P>
<P>
   Jets officials confirmed Monday they had decided to grant the
Patriots permission to speak to Vital after denying the request
last week. The change of heart came after Jets director of football
operations Bill Parcells determined that the New England position
would represent a promotion for Vital.
</P>
<P>
   After firing vice president of player personnel Bobby Grier and
national scout Dave Uyrus, and allowing scout Chris Grier _ the son
of Bobby _ to pursue a job with the Miami Dolphins, Belichick has
been hot on the trail of Vital.
</P>
<P>
   According to a Jets official, Vital is expected to finalize a
deal with the Patriots Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   Vital has worked for Belichick and Patriots executive Scott
Pioli in both Cleveland and New York.
</P>
<P>
   Pioli took a similar route to New England, as Parcells, Pioli's
father-in-law, first denied the Patriots permission to talk to him
and then reconsidered, realizing that Pioli was better served by
leaving the Jets organization and joining the Patriots staff
because of his close working ties with Belichick.
</P>
<P>
   The hiring of Vital, an African-American, will be endorsed by
Rainbow Sports, a watchdog organization for diversity in sports. At
the time Grier was fired, he was the highest-ranking black
executive in the NFL. Rainbow Sports director Charles Farrell had
said that while it was Belichick's prerogative to hire and fire as
he pleased, he was watching to see how the Patriots replaced him.
</P>
<P>
   Vital will not replace Grier per se _ Belichick has final
authority over personnel matters _ but he will hold a prominent
position. As national pro scout, Vital will be responsible for
advancing the next opponent, scouting personnel in the NFL, and
recommending free agents for the Patriots to sign.
</P>
<P>
   Vital, 37, is a native of Loreauville, La., who spent time as a
running back and kick returner for the Washington Redskins, who
drafted him in the seventh round in 1985, and Detroit Lions.
</P>
<P>
   Belichick has not been shy about raiding the Jets for front
office and coaching personnel. He has brought over offensive
coordinator Charlie Weis, secondary coach Eric Mangini, director of
pro personnel Pioli, and personal assistant Berj Najarian.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
