<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-15 21:08 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A5959 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s BC-ACC-MEETINGS-COX     05-15 0507
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ACC-MEETINGS-COX </SLUG>

<TEXT>
<P>
   Once-proud basketball league now feels need to promote
</P>
<P>
   By Stan Arey
</P>
<P>
   Amelia Island, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   The big issues at this year's annual meeting of the Atlantic
Coast Conference aren't expansion, location of the treasured
basketball tournament or the improvement of the out-of-league
football schedule.
</P>
<P>
   The big issues are marketing, public relations and promotion.
</P>
<P>
   The ACC's image as the nation's premier basketball conference
has slipped. For each of the past two seasons, the league has
managed to place only three teams in the NCAA Tournament ``I would
say that's probably right,'' associate commissioner Tom Mickle said
when asked if the marketing issue will dominate the meetings.
``We've never done any marketing before, because we didn't have to.
Now we're taking a hard look at it, and we will spend a lot of time
discussing it.''
</P>
<P>
   ``We are looking at ourselves,'' associate commissioner Fred
Baracat said. ``It's not like years ago.''
</P>
<P>
   Super conference talk
</P>
<P>
   A hot rumor on the Internet has the SEC forming a 16-team super
conference by raiding the ACC to pick off Florida State, Georgia
Tech and Clemson and then dipping into the Big East to grab Miami.
``Nobody has contacted me,'' Tech athletics director Dave Braine
said. ``(FSU athletics director) Dave Hart hasn't said anything. I
had lunch with (Clemson AD) Bobby Robinson today, and he didn't say
anything. Miami hasn't called, which I'm sure they would if
anything was going on.''
</P>
<P>
   Improving the competition
</P>
<P>
   ABC, CBS, ESPN, Fox Sports, Home Team Sports, Jefferson-Pilot,
Raycom and The Sunshine Network all came to the meetings with the
same request. The television networks are pushing for the ACC
football teams to upgrade their out-of-conference games. North
Carolina has added Syracuse, Wisconsin, Texas and Notre Dame over
the next few years. Virginia plays Penn State and Notre Dame and
always plays Virginia Tech. Clemson has added Auburn and Texas A&AMP;M.
</P>
<P>
   The requests are not new, Mickle said. ``It's a constant refrain
in any meeting regarding television.''
</P>
<P>
   The nation's richest
</P>
<P>
   The ACC continues to lead the nation in money paid out to
members. The league paid $60 million this year. That amount will
jump to $70 million by the 2001-2002 school year.
</P>
<P>
   Over the past two years, for the first time in history, football
brought in more money than basketball. Football was responsible for
$32 million this year, while basketball managed $28 million.
</P>
<P>
   The situation will change quickly, however, because the ACC
signed a new 10-year basketball contract in February. By 2002,
basketball will bring in roughly $36 million, while football will
produce $34 million.
</P>
<P>
   No announcement
</P>
<P>
   The ACC will not make an immediate announcement about the site
of the 2005 basketball tournament. Although there is little doubt
the league will go to Tampa and the Washington, D.C., area soon,
details have not been determined.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
